						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the Sōmāskanda shrine in the same temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1386, Subhānu, Tai = 1464 A.D., January.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records that a certain Araśaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vallāḷadēvar caused the Nāyakar Araṅgu-maṇḍapam <hi rend="italic">(Raṅga-Maṇḍapa)</hi> to be built and made a gift of 1/4 <hi rend="italic">nilam</hi> and a house in the western street for food-offerings to the deity (Kaḷandai Nāyakar). It is stated that the gift was a <hi rend="italic">tirunāmattukkāṇi.</hi> The name of the village is not, however, mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
